                Documentation for the Daily Price Files
          *************************************************

	The data in the A C Nielsen Household Purchase History files was
used to create files which describe the daily purchasing behavior of the
consumers as well as the prices, coupons, and advertising to which they 
were exposed at the time of their purchases.  In short, the daily price
files contain time series data for brands with a market share of at least
1%, giving for each day the consumer behavior, prices, store coupon  
information, and levels of advertising.

	Within chains whose stores had nearly identical pricing behavior, 
those stores had their prices and store coupon information calculated by
chain.  Within market 1 this includes chains 4 and 5.  The other stores were
done on an individual basis.  All stores in market 2 were done individually.

	What follows is a listing of the variables in the datasets PF1.SSD
and PF2.SSD, the price files corresponding to markets 1 (Sioux Falls, South
Dakota) and 2 (Springfield, Missouri).  The files are sorted by UPC (or PID),
by chain, by store id, by date.  Within each store id, the dates are
continuous from the Wednesday prior to the first observation in the HP file
to the Tuesday following the last.



Name		Type	Length			Description
****		****	******		*************************

UPC or PID	num	  7		Upc or product id number

CHAIN		num       3		Store chain number

SID		num       3		Store id number

DATE		num       4		Date in SAS format(i.e. number of
					  days since January 1, 1960)

DPR		num       4		Daily price or 'deal' price

REG		num       4		Regular price

CUT		num       4		Manufacturer sponsored price cut
					(Note: this only applies with the
						dry detergent datasets)

UNITS		num       4		Total number of units purchased 
					  in the store that day

SCIND		num       3		Store coupon indicator. (1 if
					  there were store coupons available,
					  0 if not)

SCUNITS		num       4		Total number of units purchased on
					  store coupons that day

SCVAL		num       4		Modal value of the store coupons
					  redeemed that day	

MCIND		num       3		Manufacturer coupon indicator.
					  (1 if a manufacturer coupon was
					  redeemed that day, 0 if not)

MCUNITS		num       4		Total number of units purchased on
					  manufacturer coupons that day

AMCV		num       4		Average value of manufacturer coupons
					  redeemed that day

LINE		num       3		Line-advertisment indicator

MAJOR		num       3		Major-advertisment indicator

DISPLAY		num       3		Display (of any type) indicator 





